review_blob:
Tap @ Speakeasy by Phjala.

Very deep dark ruby color, light carbonation. Nice rich aroma of vanilla, some dried exotic fruits even - reminds me of bourbon Makers Mark. Taste is very intense, complex, with lots of woody, vanilla, coconut notes, though alcohol isnt well hidden. Aftertaste is slight bitter, quite hard to drink. Overall - good BA beer, shall be better after ageing in bottles.
beer_name: Phjala Cellar Series - Odravein 2015 Bourbon BA

review_blob: Tap @ Speakeasy by Phjala. Quite intensive aroma of chocolate liquor, spices and licorice. Very sweet, with tons of spices, like star anise, cardamon, cinnamon, reminds of British Christmas pudding, some hints of strong booze, like whiskey or strong liquor. Would be great food pair both with verevorstid (estonian blood sausage with cowberry jam) and chocolate cake, but would prefer first. Excellent brew, but little bit too sweet. Hope they will make a bottle version also.
beer_name: Phjala / To l Cellar Series - Taanilinn Cognac BA

review_blob: Wow! Such a rich citrus flavor with mild honey and elderflower notes. The bomb for your taste sensors, absolutely a must try!
Bottle. Fresh tropical smell, amazingly rich taste of fruits, white bread and nuts, strong bitterness in the end. Great pair with hot food!
Bottle. Amber color, almost no head. Smell of honey and fruits, taste of sweet caramel, vanilla and white raisins. Just a slight bitterness in the end, Pretty good stuff, worth a try!

Bottle. Dark colour, nice aroma of blackberries, cocoa and alcohol. Taste almost the same, with some dark chocolate notes. Not a massive aftertaste, but still very good. Nice beer, but too strong smell and taste of alcohol.

Bottle. Rich dark color of noble imperial stout. Almost no head. On the nose: treacle, alcohol, honey and nuts. Taste: coffee, dried plums and chocolate. Pretty long aftertaste, quite good. Nothing fantastic here - little bit boring, getting tired of this taste pretty soon. But definitely worth a try.
Bottle. Excellent smell of citrus and freshly cut grass, taste of dried fruits and long aftertaste contains essence of apples. peaches and mild bitterness. I love this beer, its almost perfect.

Bottle. Cloudy brown color, pretty strong smell of citrus and pine oil, tastes wonderful with a hint of lime wedge and some warm spices, typical pleasant bitterness at the end. Not outstanding beer - just one of a kind, pretty good though.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: Pretty carbonated with very dark opaque color. Has slight chocolate and coffee aroma and taste, bitterness in the end.
beer_name: Bernard ern Lek 12 / Bernard Dark Lager

review_blob: Has great espresso and dark maple syrup aroma, tastes quite sweet and delicious, with a hint of cinnamon and bitterness in the end.
Great pale ale with very strong aftertaste. Fruity notes, honey, bitter chocolate in the end. Highly enjoyable.
